. С 2019-го рынок утроился.\n\nОтвет Gambling Commission: открыли вакансию Head of Illegal Markets. Зарплата - £65,000 в год.\n\nРынок £16 миллиардов. Один человек.\n\n@vipcare_io", "image_html": null}], "linkedin_post": {"text": "LINKEDIN POST:\n\nUK regulators spent six years tightening VIP controls. The black market just tripled.\n\nNew data from the Betting and Gaming Council shows £16.6 billion is now wagered annually with unlicensed UK operators - triple the 2019 figure, and doubled in just two years. The Gambling Commission's response? A new \"Head of Illegal Markets\" role, advertised at £65,000 per year.\n\nFor VIP managers, the signal is clear: when licensed operators over-restrict, players don't stop gambling. They find an environment that treats them like adults. No affordability checks. No account closures. No source-of-funds requests.\n\nThe best operators I've spoken to are already rethinking the balance. Compliance is non-negotiable - but how you engage a high-value player inside the rules matters enormously. The operators losing VIPs to the black market aren't losing because of regulation. They're losing because they forgot that experience drives loyalty, not restrictions.\n\nThe £65K hire won't solve a £16 billion problem. But the operators who understand why players left - and fix that within the rules - will.\n\n#iGaming #VIPRetention #CasinoOperations #PlayerExperience"}}